This paper discusses the development of a new paradigm for network security, specifically for BYOD policies. The paper focuses on the use of programmable switches, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses security concerns and the need for context-aware policies, which falls under the categories of security and privacy (cs.CR), systems and control (cs.SY), software engineering (cs.SE), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
